news.title: Jaipur metro phase II work to kick off by Diwali, completion in five years
news.para: While the previous Line 1 project, implemented during the Congress govt's tenure, was fully funded by the state, Line 2 will be a joint venture between the union and state govts.

news.title: Bengaluru development body plans expansion of Karanth Layout project
news.para: ​In a major step, BDA is considering acquiring an additional 3,000 acres spread across 18 villages in Yelahanka and Bengaluru North taluk to continue building on the success of the current phase.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA to e-auction attached properties, ropes in MSTC
news.para: The authority took the decision of using the e-auction software of MSTC, widely used by govt departments, as it seeks to enforce compliance and ensure timely recovery from defaulting real estate developers.

news.title: NBCC’s Kidwai Nagar project caught in GST crossfire between ministries
news.para: A GST demand on NBCC's escrow fund for the Kidwai Nagar redevelopment project has sparked a conflict between the Urban Development and Finance Ministries. The DGGI issued the notice, arguing that lease receipts collected by NBCC are subject to GST.

news.title: Ultra rich betting on trophy properties to preserve wealth
news.para: This surge in high-value purchases by promoters and family trusts in cities like Mumbai, New Delhi, and Bengaluru reflects a broader shift in capital management strategies, family office experts said.

news.title: AU Small Finance Bank buys commercial tower in Mumbai’s Bandra for ₹371 crore
news.para: The Jaipur-headquartered bank has purchased the 11-storey property with two basements spread over 74,577 sq ft to set up its corporate office in Mumbai.

news.title: Singapore's CapitaLand Ascendas REIT to buy two properties for $543.6 million
news.para: The REIT said the acquisitions will increase the value of its Singapore portfolio by 6% to approximately S$11.7 billion. Both properties are fully leased to "reputable tenants", the company added, guaranteeing stable and predictable income streams.

news.title: Government invites suggestions on draft Registration Bill 2025
news.para: ​The Department of Land Resources, Ministry of Rural Development, has prepared the draft 'The Registration Bill 2025', which once enacted will replace the pre-Constitution law -- The Registration Act, 1908.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's net profit grows 19.20% in Q4 FY25
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's net consolidated total income stood at ₹1,913.55 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 5.89 per cent from ₹1,807.15 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shriram Properties' net profit up 136.41% in Q4 FY25
news.para: Shriram Properties' net consolidated total income stood at ₹427.51 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 19.29 per cent from ₹358.37 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: India’s most impactful real estate events & conferences to watch
news.para: Best real estate events & conferences in India: From marquee summits to regional dialogues, the country’s leading real estate forums are setting the stage for future-ready development. Whether you're an Owner, builder, architect, investor, or urban policy stakeholder, these curated event platforms by ETRealty offer insights, visibility, and strategic connections.

news.title: NCW Prime Offices Fund acquires Prius Platinum in Delhi
news.para: Spanning across 0.3 million sq ft, the property was acquired from a fund managed by Kotak Alternate Asset Managers led consortium through the IBC process in 2021.

news.title: Action Construction Equipment's net profit rises 20.43% in Q4 FY25
news.para: Action Construction Equipment's net consolidated total income stood at ₹969.38 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 13.14 per cent from ₹856.76 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: BDA initiates town planning scheme implementation in Dasapur and Malipada
news.para: This is TP scheme Nos. 5, 6 and 7, which fall in zone I of the BDA. The TP scheme implementation holds importance as BDA has already proposed to develop a Bhubaneswar New City in the same area, which will cover 400 hectares of land.

news.title: Over four lakh property owners in Bengaluru under scanner for evading tax notices
news.para: Officials found many property owners misused the self-declaration system by under reporting property size to intentionally lower their property tax payments

news.title: Housing societies protest against Manesar civic body's sanitation charge
news.para: In what residents call an "arbitrary and coercive" collection under the guise of municipal taxation, MCM has appended sanitation tax to their property tax bills even though no civic worker has ever entered their compounds for waste pickup.

news.title: Chandigarh selected for pilot phase of Naksha project to digitise urban land records
news.para: The coverage area in Chandigarh includes five villages — Sarangpur, Burail, Kajheri, Palsora, and Attawa — and Sectors 2 to 17 (excluding Sector 13), encompassing a total area of 30.61 square kilometres with a population of 1.48 lakh.

news.title: Assam CM reviews progress of upcoming satellite townships, new central business district
news.para: Assam Chief Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma directed the officials to step up the construction work for the upcoming satellite township at Palasbari in Kamrup district.

news.title: Top 10 cement firms to add 140 MMTPA capacity in five years: Moody's
news.para: ​Over the past five years, the cement sector in India has witnessed significant industry consolidation and top 10 producers in the country have acquired around 140 MMTPA of domestic cement capacity, valued at around Rs 890 billion, from smaller regional players, Moody's said.

news.title: Registration of plots in illegal colonies of Indore to be declared void
news.para: ​The official said that builders who developed illegal colonies would be made to return the amount paid by plot holders as the price of the property
